<TEXT>
amnesty international appealed to indonesia not to 
execute six political prisoners who have been jailed more than 20 
years for participation in a 1965 coup attempt 
in a letter to president suharto made public friday the human 
rights groups secretarygeneral ian martin said amnesty 
international had received reports that appeals for clemency had 
been rejected 
he said his londonbased organization had heard the suharto 
government was to execute ruslan widjayasastra sukatno iskandar 
subekti asep suryaman i bungkus and marsudi on sunday 
their executions would bring to 32 the number of prisoners slain 
since 1985 compared with four in the preceding 10 years he said 
four other prisoners accused of involvement in the 1965 coup 
attempt were executed feb 13 after more than 24 years in jail 
martin said amnesty international was concerned that it is 
political prisoners who have been the principal victims of these 
judicial killings 
in the letter released to the news media martin said the six 
elderly prisoners had been convicted of membership in the communist 
party of indonesia and of involvement in the failed coup in 1965 
the attempt to depose president sukarno began sept 30 1965 it 
was crushed within 48 hours by troops led by suharto then a 
majorgeneral 
in the crackdown that followed up to 500000 people were 
killed more than half a million people were detained before calm 
was restored in march 1966 and suharto took power from sukarno 
</TEXT>
