stormie jones the worlds first heartliver 
transplant recipient was discharged from the hospital 17 days 
after undergoing a second liver transplant 
the 12yearold texas girl will remain in the city for about two 
weeks for outpatient treatment at childrens hospital of 
pittsburgh hospital spokeswoman lynn mcmahon said friday 
stormie received her second liver transplant in a 10hour 
operation feb 20 she had undergone a heartandliver transplant 
in 1984 
the heart has not caused any problems but she needed a new 
liver because the first was damaged by hepatitis ms mcmahon said 
surgeons are pleased with her progress 
the sixthgrader told reporters thursday she hoped to return 
home to the fort worth suburb of white settlement within a month 
