william r burleigh has been elected executive 
vice president of the ew scripps co and nominated to serve on 
its board of directors the communications company announced 
burleigh previously was senior vice president for newspapers and 
publishing at scripps 
bill burleigh has proved himself to be one of the newspaper 
industrys top managers lawrence a leser scripps president and 
chief executive officer said friday in his new role he will 
work closely with me on all facets of corporate affairs as well as 
continue to supervise our publishing operations 
the ew scripps co operates 19 daily newspapers nine 
television stations five radio stations and cable television 
systems with 558000 basic subscribers the company also is a 
worldwide syndicator and licenser of news features and comics 
burleigh was elected executive vice president thursday 
shareholders will elect directors at their may 14 annual meeting 
here 
burleigh 54 has been with scripps more than 38 years 
beginning his career while still in high school as a parttime 
sportswriter at the evansville ind press 
after his service with the us military and graduation from 
marquette university burleigh returned to the newspaper as a 
reporter he was named editor and president of the newspaper in 
1975 and served as editor of the cincinnati post from 1977 to 1983 
he joined the scripps corporate staff in 1984 as vice president 
and general editorial manager in 1986 he was promoted to senior 
vice president 
burleigh is a member of the board of directors of the associated 
press president of the american society of newspaper editors 
foundation and on the advisory board of marquettes college of 
communications 
he and his wife anne have three children 
