<TEXT>
redoubt volcano spewed a column of 
steam seven miles long on a day when three moderate earthquakes 
jolted the region 
shallow tremors around the volcano late friday led scientists at 
the alaska volcano observatory to keep a close watch on the 
volcano scientists predicted another explosion in the next few 
weeks as redoubt rebuilds its dome 
accompanied by a rare lightning storm redoubt belched steam at 
951 am ast the plume carried little ash and drifted mostly to 
the north and northwest away from population centers 
a quake centered 50 miles beneath redoubt and measuring 55 on 
the richter scale hit at 324 am friday seismologists said 
the second quake at 803 am was centered about 170 miles 
southwest of fairbanks and registered 55 on the richter scale 
a third quake registering 52 and centered 65 miles southwest 
of anchorage struck at 511 pm it shook office fixtures in 
anchorage but caused no apparent damage authorities said 
redoubt 115 miles southwest of anchorage began erupting in 
middecember after slumbering for 25 years 
on feb 28 an eruption of abrasive ash reached anchorage 
closing schools forcing precautionary evacuations at an oil 
terminal on the banks of the drift river which flows off the 
volcano 
