hungarian counterpart gyula horn the report said 
hungary is the second warsaw pact country to negotiate a 
complete withdrawal of soviet troops 
prague and moscow reached an agreement last month on the removal 
of 73500 soviet troops from czechoslovakia the pullout there 
began feb 26 
such pullouts were requested after prodemocracy revolutions 
swept communists from power across eastern europe late last year 
and early this year 
the signing of the hungariansoviet agreement came just one day 
after negotiations were completed on its terms and a timetable for 
the withdrawal 
there had been initial disagreement over the date for the 
pullout to be completed but the two sides finally agreed that all 
troops and equipment should be withdrawn by june 30 1991 thats 
the same date that the withdrawal from czechoslovakia is to be 
finished 
the soviets reportedly had wanted the hungarian withdrawal to be 
completed on aug 31 1991 to give them more time for dismantling 
military stockpiles but agreed to the earlier date sought by the 
hungarians 
there are 49700 soviet soldiers in hungary as well as 27146 
combat vehicles including 860 tanks and 1500 armored personnel 
carriers accoriding to hungarian military officials 
according to the hungarian radio report twothirds of the 
withdrawal of soviet forces and equipment is to be completed by the 
end of this year 
horn traveled to moscow today the agreement was initialed 
friday by the heads of the two delegations negotiating the terms of 
the withdrawal 
attending the final round of talks that ended in moscow on 
friday were three hungarian observers representing opposition 
parties competing in national elections march 25 they are to be 
the first free multiparty elections since the communists 
consolidated power in 1948 
</TEXT>
