after the speakers had finished wrestling with the 
subject of their symposium germany in the 1990s jewish hopes 
and fears an old whitehaired man in the audience struggled to 
his feet 
everybody says reunification of germany is unavoidable but is 
everybody really happy about this forthcoming reunification he 
said i a refugee from vienna in 1939 am not and i suspect 
that there must be many people here who equally are not happy 
his remarks encapsulated the unease and helplessness felt by 
many western european jews although clearly not all at the 
prospect of a united germany 
it is happening too soon it is happening too fast said 
