documentary shoah 
germany is a special country he said in a telephone 
interview from paris one cannot guess now what this new germany 
will be what the contradictions and the tensions will be inside 
this country the new german nationalism will have in my opinion 
a very strong revival 
nobody can say calmly today that this new germany will behave 
like the former federal republic of west germany lanzmann said 
the london symposiums audience consisted mostly of elderly jews 
holocaust survivors refugees people who had achieved peace and 
prosperity in britain but were still sufficiently preoccupied with 
the nazi past to crowd into a basement auditorium and air their 
fears 
reassurances that there could never be another hitler were 
coupled with vaguely expressed fears for the future a man spoke of 
this feeling of impotence in the face of a german giant risen 
again 
like a dark backdrop to the proceedings lay the fears jews feel 
about reawakened antisemitism in the soviet union and in eastern 
and central europe 
no matter what the structure will be at this moment as jews 
as people who have often experienced germany at its worst we have 
great fears that cannot be easily laid aside said albert 
