<TEXT>
former president richard nixon was making his 
first visit to the house since being driven from office by the 
watergate scandal when rep newt gingrich learned that his own 
ethics cloud had evaporated 
gingrich secondranking republican in the house said it was 
during nixons hourlong meeting thursday with gop members of 
congress that he was handed the letter ending 11 psychologically 
difficult months 
the letter said the committee had dismissed ethics complaints 
brought by rep bill alexander dark against the georgia 
lawmaker after he had caused the investigation that led to the 
resignation of former speaker jim wright dtexas 
the committee however criticized gingrich for not reporting on 
his annual financial disclosure forms that he had cosigned the 
mortgage on his daughters home it also criticized gingrich for 
his staffs use of official letterhead to promote a private 
companys senior citizens cruise 
but on each of alexanders major allegations of misconduct the 
committee said it found that no adequate basis existed to 
launch a fullscale ethics investigation 
most of the allegations focused on a partnership gingrich 
created in 1984 to promote a book he helped write window of 
opportunity alexander contended gingrich had violated house 
rules on gifts and outside income as well as federal campaign 
finance laws with the partnership and book deal 
the committees letter capped gingrichs meteoric rise in less 
than two years from a backbench republican firebrand to the 
leading contender to replace 67yearold republican leader bob 
michel when he retires 
along the way gingrichs tactics made him the target of choice 
for house democrats 
gingrich compiled lists of democrats he claimed should be 
investigated he traveled the country denouncing house democratic 
corruption and he filed the complaint that led the ethics 
committee to charge wright with 69 violations of house rules 
including charges that he accepted 145000 in gifts from a fort 
worth texas business executive 
as the ethics investigation grew more serious for wright house 
republicans rewarded gingrich by electing him whip last year when 
dick cheney left the job to become secretary of defense democrats 
vowed revenge when wright decided to resign last june 
theres no question democrats were mad as hell and wanted to 
pin him to the wall after wright was forced from office said 
