but mann said gingrich benefited both from the changed 
atmosphere in the house since wrights resignation and from the 
apparent weakness of the charges 
politically motivated charges arent going to go anywhere 
unless theres something really there to begin with and unless the 
overall atmosphere that made it possible remains the same he 
said 
when he resigned wright called for an end to mindless 
cannibalism and the new democratic leadership team moved to 
reduce the partisan tone in the house 
but gingrich said hes convinced the committee would have 
reached the same conclusion in his case anyway 
on item after item after item they said there is no grounds 
for these charges gingrich said so my presumption is that 
even in a more intensely partisan environment the truth beats 
passion in the end 
with the ethics case resolved in gingrichs favor mann 
predicted democrats likely will reorient their campaign but not 
abandon it 
they still want to get him but i think it will switch from 
ethics and legal wars to political wars he said 
