hundreds of residential houses and public facilities were also 
damaged sameer said 
a purge of forces loyal to tanai continued saturday government 
sources reported arrests among officials in the state television 
station and among lowerranking officers in the military and the 
security forces 
five members of the ruling politburo five members of the 
national defense council and two members of the central committee 
of the ruling peoples democratic party of afghanistan have been 
purged bakhtar news agency reported 
one eastern european source quoting afghan government 
officials said more than 2000 people were jailed wednesday and 
thursday the reports could not be independently confirmed 
of the arrests sameer would say only we have arrested a 
number of people involved in the coup plot and will continue to 
arrest others 
the losses of men and equipment appeared likely to weaken the 
fighting strength of the afghan army which remains locked in civil 
war with the usbacked rebels the western military expert said 
the afghan air force which was the center of the coup attempt 
has been credited in large part with helping najib survive since 
the kremlin ended nine years of military intervention in february 
1989 
but it also seemed unlikely guerrilla forces would be able to 
capitalize on the chaos they remained in relative disunity 
diplomats based in kabul said 
afghan government radio and television continued to link tanais 
plot to fundamentalist rebel leader gulbuddin hekmatyar but 
diplomats in kabul said they believed the rebel leader had nothing 
to do with the operation 
hekmatyar has said however he supports the coup and is 
