the us district court that serves 
georgias southern district has become the first in the nation to 
get its own flag 
the red white and blue flag designed by clerk henry r crumley 
jr and given official recognition in a dec 8 court order by chief 
judge anthony a alaimo will be displayed in each federal 
courtroom in the 43county district 
david sellers spokesman for the washington administrative 
office of all us courts said friday that he knows of no other 
court district in the nation that has its own flag 
crumley said he and alaimo felt the judiciary as the third 
branch of government should have its own flag most federal 
agencies already have flags 
his court flag has a white stripe through the middle separating 
its red top and blue bottom in the center is the great seal of the 
united states 
curved above the seal are the words united states courts 
and below are the words southern district of georgia 
crumley said the red symbolizes the blood that has been shed to 
preserve the judicial system the white the purity of the system 
and the blue the commitment of the courts to upholding the law 
people who have seen it think its beautiful said crumley 
