<TEXT>
the first us nuclear weapon test of 1990 
rocked the nevada desert saturday the same day a published report 
said the soviet union is phasing out testing on its mainland 
because of citizens safety concerns 
the washington post reported that the soviet union would move 
its nuclear testing site from southcentral asia to an island 
inside the arctic circle it cited sources it did not name in the 
soviet union and the united states 
the tested weapon codenamed metropolis was detonated at the 
bottom of a 1500foot shaft at yucca flat at the remote nevada 
test site the device was listed as having an explosive force of 
20000 to 150000 tons of tnt but was believed to be near the 
upper limits because of warnings issued in advance by the energy 
department 
the test registered 51 on the richter scale at the national 
earthquake information center in golden colo according to 
spokesman john minsch 
seismic equipment atop fitzgeralds hotel and casino in downtown 
las vegas 85 miles away registered slight motion from the blast 
theres definitely ground motion doe spokesman chris west 
said by telephone from a control point 12 miles from ground zero 
where the test was monitored by video camera 
its a little like sitting in a rowboat in the water theres 
a mild rocking motion west said 
he said 11 antinuclear weapons protesters turned out at a gate 
about 30 miles from ground zero shortly before the 8 am 
detonation two protesters were arrested on trespassing charges 
the washington post said the soviets had decided to phase out 
nuclear testing at their main testing grounds at seimipalatinsk in 
southcentral asia and halt testing there by 1993 the soviets 
plan to shift their testing program to novaya zemlya a large 
island in the barents sea within the arctic circle the sources 
told the paper 
a russian antinuclear group named nevada has been campaigning 
to halt testing at semipalatinsk complaining of radiation leaks 
from the underground tests 
the soviets have had a second major test site for many years 
and have done a lot of testing there west said saturday the 
soviets are not stopping testing but are just moving to another 
location the us doesnt have the luxury of a backup site 
metropolis was the 700th announced test conducted in nevada 
since testing began at the desert site in 1951 the last test was 
dec 20 
