<TEXT>
jackson martindell a management 
consultant and former publisher of whos who in america has died 
of cancer he was 89 
martindell who died wednesday was born in amarillo texas and 
was a graduate of the university of colorado and columbia 
university he served in the armys american expeditionary force 
during world war i 
by 1932 martindell was in new york city and had founded 
fiduciary counsel inc which advised prominent business families 
he also was treasurer of the marshall field foundation 
over the next two decades martindell made a reputation as a 
banker financier consultant and economic adviser 
after world war ii he worked as a us government volunteer to 
help the yugoslavian government reestablish that nations economy 
in 1948 he married anne clark who later became a new jersey 
state senator and us ambassador to new zealand 
in 1949 martindell founded the new american institute of 
management which developed the management audit technique to 
assess business leadership for many years he ran the company from 
his fort lauderdale home 
in 1956 he became publisher of marquis whos who of chicago 
which published the annual whos who in america he sold the 
publication to itt in 1969 for a sum he described as fantastic 
and retired 
he is survived by three sons and a daughter 
