effect was almost immediate in alabama alone he said black voter 
registration increased from about 92000 in 1964 to nearly 250000 
in 1967 
nationwide the number of black elected officials has leaped 
from 103 in 1964 to 7226 today turner told the rally 
the final twomile leg of the commemoration began about two 
hours before the capitol ceremony with lowery and mrs king 
leading about 1000 blacks and a few whites through some of 
montgomerys black neighborhoods 
