<TEXT>
italian communists applauded and sang 
saturday after party leader achille occhetto moved to tears by the 
embrace of his chief opponents made an impassioned call for unity 
in creating a new party 
occhetto has emerged victorious at the party congress in his 
effort to relaunch the italian communist party a move that 
eventually is expected to lead to a new party name and the 
elimination of the hammerandsickle symbol 
delegates representing the wests largest communist party began 
voting at about 1120 pm on the proposal but the result was 
assured and delegates passed resolutions during the evening to 
regulate how they will plan for the new party 
the party said the voting booths would be open for three hours 
and the result would be announced later sunday the final vote had 
been expected earlier but was backed up behind a series of 
resolutions and speeches 
we want to change many things but we do not intend to leave 
the historic path from which we came we want to widen it said 
occhetto 
together we will construct our future we will struggle 
together for democracy for italy and for europe and socialism 
occhettos proposal was spurred by the collapse of communism in 
eastern europe and the partys steady decline in membership and 
electoral strength in italy 
occetto was interrupted by applause 24 times during the 
hourlong speech he urged unity and outlined how the new party 
would seek to create a democratic alternative in italy to 
represent the workers the poor the weak and the disenfranchised 
the party leader came to the congress with the support of almost 
67 percent of the delegates that was more than enough to ensure 
the success of his bid to create a new party 
however his proposal risks splitting the party which claims 
14 million members 
old guard communists waged an impassioned battle against 
revisions which were expected to include the name change and 
elimination of the partys revered symbols 
but fears of a party split seemed to vanish when the partys old 
lion pietro ingrao and former party secretary alessandro natta 
two of the leading opponents of change embraced occhetto at the 
end of his speech 
the 1092 delegates gave occhetto a standing ovation applauding 
and singing bandiera rosa red flag the party anthem 
occhetto wiped tears from his eyes as he took his seat on the high 
red multitiered platform the sports arena was awash in red 
banners and communist symbols 
the communists nearly came to power in 1976 when they won 34 
percent of the vote but they dropped to about 27 percent in the 
last parliamentary elections in 1987 
the italian party has long proclaimed itself independent of 
moscow it has espoused western parliamentary democracy supported 
italys membership in nato and condemned the soviet intervention in 
czechoslovakia in 1968 and afghanistan in 1979 
but while the party has portrayed itself as a critic of 
international communism occhetto has argued it cannot ignore the 
march of history and the collapse of communist governments in 
eastern europe 
he has maintained that a revamped italian party can move closer 
to the mainstream of european socialism and perhaps unite italys 
fractured political left to offer an alternative to the christian 
democrats who have dominated italian politics more than four 
decades 
