he had been spying for israel mrs parish did not appear in the 
broadcast 
the editor of the sunday observer donald trelford said the 
paper was certain bazoft was not spying for anyone he said the 
statement must have been made under duress and noted that bazoft 
appeared to be in poor physical shape 
trelford said bazoft had sought official permission to visit the 
aliskandaria military complex south of baghdad had told the paper 
of his movements and had talked openly about the visit to 
colleagues on his return to baghdad 
none of this conduct is consistent with espionage it is 
entirely consistent with journalism he said 
