<TEXT>
portauprince haiti ap when lt gen prosper avril came to 
power in in 1988 he talked of free elections and leading the 
country toward democracy 
saturday it was avril himself who was on the move he was 
forced from power in a popular uprising by opponents who feared he 
would not make good on his promises 
like many haitian rulers avril came to power in violence and 
left in violence 
a week before the september 1988 coup that brought him to power 
thugs armed with machetes guns and spears stormed the roman 
catholic church of the rev bertrand aristide a popular government 
critic they massacred a dozen people there 
the bloodbath split the military and lowerranking soldiers 
revolted against lt henri namphy he was the army chief of staff 
who took charge of the government after dictator jeanclaude 
duvalier fled to france in february 1986 during another mass 
uprising 
the 1988 soldiers rebellion was apparently not orchestrated by 
avril then army chief of staff but it was avril who finally came 
out on top declaring himself president 
he quickly went on national television and promised the 
impoverished caribbean nation democratic reform and free 
presidential elections haitians accustomed to lies and brutality 
from their leaders were skeptical 
avril a 52yearold with a quiet demeanor never seemed 
comfortable in the public eye his wife marieange is a captain 
in the army and a nurse the couple has four children 
avril had been in the background as a financial adviser to 
francois papa doc duvalier jeanclaudes father who founded 
the 29year duvalier family regime avril later advised duvaliers 
son when he replaced his father 
because of that close relationship critics called avril a 
bagman who reputedly became a millionaire and negotiated 
military weapons and equipment sales abroad 
meanwhile the duvaliers created an authoritarian regime using 
the dreaded forces known as tonton macoutes to keep opponents in 
check 
despite his earlier association with the duvaliers avril won 
some public support a few months into his rule he held public 
meetings with civilian political leaders talked with union leaders 
and restored most of the 1987 constitution that namphy suspended 
he also approved the formation of an independent electoral 
council to organize and oversee this years general elections 
although there was skepticism many thought it was better to 
work with avril than against him 
youre not going to get power if theres not a reasonable 
understanding with those guys marc bazin a presidential hopeful 
and former world bank economist said at the time 
the us government has had mixed feelings about avrils regime 
in its human rights report it said the haitian army was linked to 
human rights abuses in rural areas but that it avoided the 
egregious violations massacres and politically motivated killings 
characteristic of his predecessors 
nevertheless in march 1989 it said the resumption of 60 
million in aid must be tied to democratic reform and cooperation in 
fighting drug trafficking immediately afterward avrils 
government accused four highranking army officers of drug 
trafficking and discharged them 
