the treasury departmentled rtc oversight board which controls 
the policy and pursestrings of the bailout approved a change 
designed to speed the sale of repossessed real estate it 
authorized the corporation to accept down payments as low as 15 
percent a reduction from 25 percent 
the federal housing finance board announced it had allowed the 
first two commercial banks to join the federal home loan bank 
system membership in the system created in 1934 to provide 
lowcost financing for home mortgages had previously been 
restricted to savings institutions 
the sampl law enacted last august allows banks and credit unions 
to join if they devote at least 10 percent of their assets to 
residential housing the two new members are the national bank of 
bremerton bremerton wash and north american bank and trust co 
waterbury conn 
