corporate raiders once used junk bonds like 
kryptonite to intimidate companies with takeover forays 
but the sagging market for junk has given potential targets a 
lead shield to protect themselves and the raiders are resorting to 
other less powerful weapons 
the latest example came this past week when usx corp harried 
by carl icahn consented to his proposal for a nonbinding 
shareholder vote on whether the company should vacate the steel 
business 
icahn usxs largest shareholder once could have taken much 
more drastic action ultimately a hostile takeover backed by 
billions of dollars in borrowed money provided by eager banks and 
