said friday that their attempts to prod the giant oil company into 
a more environmentally sensitive direction could include a call at 
exxons annual meeting to oust its chairman 
six shareholder proposals on environmental issues have been 
cleared by the securities and exchange commission for inclusion in 
exxons proxy statement and will be voted on at the companys april 
25 annual meeting 
the company opposes all six proposals which among other things 
call for exxon to take leadership in dealing with the damage 
caused by its alaska oil spill 
another resolution for an environmental report card based on the 
valdez principles which is a set of corporate guidelines calling 
for conservation restoration of damaged environments reduction of 
wastes and other moves to protect the environment 
shareholders were unable to get such measures in the proxy 
statement last year because the huge oil spill in alaska which 
created a lingering public outcry against exxon occurred after the 
deadline for submitting resolutions 
instead shareholders including some representing pension funds 
with large holdings of exxon stock had to be content with 
questioning company leaders about the spill and demanding greater 
accountability 
as occurred last year some shareholders again are likely to ask 
at the annual meeting for the resignation of lawrence g rawl 
exxons chairman and chief executive officer said gray davis 
trustee for the california public employee retirement system the 
nations largest public pension fund 
ive never seen a less concerned and less tuned in ceo said 
