<TEXT>
rep glenn english says he may 
reluctantly support a user fee on futures trades to fund tougher 
enforcement by the industrys federal regulator the commodity 
futures trading commission 
in a speech friday to the futures industry associations annual 
convention english also criticized the securities and exchange 
commissions bid for jurisdiction over stockindex futures calling 
it a bureaucratic power grab 
english dokla sponsored a cftc reauthorization bill passed 
last year by the house the bill would increase the agencys budget 
by about 30 percent to 44 million over the next two years to pay 
for tougher policing of the nations futures exchanges 
the bush administration has proposed an 11cent user fee on 
every futures transaction to provide nearly all of the cftcs 
revenue a plan the industry strongly opposes 
english who chairs a house credit subcommittee with cftc 
oversight authority said he might support a smaller user fee to 
pay only for the proposed increase in the agencys budget the 
chicago mercantile exchange has said it could back such a plan 
english said he usually opposes user fees which he also called 
taxes 
but he said that given the realities of the budget we face 
today if we can find no other way to meet the funding requirements 
that we have authorized in the house and senate legislation i 
would very reluctantly accept user fees in making up that 
difference 
a version of englishs bill has been approved by the senate 
agriculture committee and a senate vote is expected after easter 
user fees and jurisdictional issues are among the concerns being 
addressed by congress in the debate over cftc reauthorization in 
the wake of the 1987 stockmarket crash and the federal 
investigation of trading fraud at the chicago board of trade and 
chicago merc 
on the question of regulatory jurisdiction over stockindex 
futures english said the sec is outmoded and lacks the expertise 
to effectively regulate futures markets 
the sec which regulates the stock and bond markets has been 
gaining congressional support in its longrunning battle for 
control over index futures which are regulated by the cftc 
stockindex futures which are based on such indexes as the 
standard amp poors 500stock index enable investors to speculate 
on the stock markets general trend without actually having to buy 
hundreds of different issues 
strategies involving the simultaneous trading of stockindex 
futures and the stocks they represent known as index arbitrage 
has been blamed by some for causing excessive price volatility in 
the stock market 
but english said the sec has no business in the futures markets 
the securities and exchange commission has been living on 
its reputation and may in fact be archaic and oldfashioned in many 
of their methods english said 
he said the recent collapse of of the junkbond giant drexel 
burnham lambert inc raised serious questions about whether the 
sec can handle their own business much less anyone elses 
